by GromNaN at 2015-03-06T17:46:32Z

`OPTIONS` has a very specific use-case. You can use [stack-cors](https://github.com/asm89/stack-cors) to handle this method properly.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by jimdoescode at 2015-03-06T18:12:18Z

Right, it has a very specific use case but not as specific a response structure. I'd rather manually handle OPTIONS requests because then I can add any optional headers, or even a response, based on the specific route requested. Middleware (like stack-cors) wouldn't give as much flexibility as defining independent routes would.

