by jimdoescode at 2015-05-08T15:15:54Z

It surprises me that usage wouldn't be that widespread considering the surge in JavaScript web apps over the past few years. Some browsers like Chrome wont even complete an AJAX request until an OPTIONS request is successfully handled.

But I guess it's not too hard to implement separately and if someone does want the ability to do that they can extend Application or switch to [Slim Framework for it.](http://docs.slimframework.com/routing/options/)

